in great, what does it say?

00:32:10.419 --> 00:32:14.940
Great fear came upon, what's the next word say?

00:32:16.220 --> 00:32:17.419
All the church.

00:32:18.559 --> 00:32:20.539
And upon as many as what?

00:32:21.479 --> 00:32:23.360
Heard these things.

00:32:24.360 --> 00:32:27.080
Does verse 11 make sense to you?

00:32:27.080 --> 00:32:28.559
Knowing verses one through 10?

00:32:29.759 --> 00:32:31.319
Come on.

00:32:31.319 --> 00:32:32.759
If you know verse one through 10,

00:32:32.759 --> 00:32:37.199
if you were there and you observed it and you saw it,

00:32:37.199 --> 00:32:39.639
and then the Bible says in great fear.

00:32:39.639 --> 00:32:41.360
Yep, absolutely.

00:32:41.360 --> 00:32:44.360
Came upon all, absolutely, not just some of us,

00:32:44.360 --> 00:32:46.839
not just most of us, but all of us.

00:32:46.839 --> 00:32:48.039
That what?

00:32:48.039 --> 00:32:51.919
All the church and upon as many as heard these things.

00:32:51.919 --> 00:32:54.479
What was the problem back in Exodus chapter number nine?

00:32:54.479 --> 00:32:58.639
Notice the Bible says he that feared the word of the Lord.

00:32:58.639 --> 00:33:00.319
And then it says in he that regarded

00:33:00.319 --> 00:33:01.639
not the word of the Lord.

00:33:01.639 --> 00:33:04.559
I believe that it's not a stretch for us to say in verse 21

00:33:04.559 --> 00:33:06.720
that those people that regarded not the word of the Lord,

00:33:06.720 --> 00:33:08.580
they feared not the word of the Lord.

00:33:10.119 --> 00:33:12.199
And then we come to Acts chapter number five

00:33:12.199 --> 00:33:14.399
and we see that here in this text of scripture,

00:33:14.399 --> 00:33:17.559
the Bible says that great fear came upon all the church

00:33:17.559 --> 00:33:21.440
and upon as many as heard these things.

00:33:21.959 --> 00:33:25.199
Now I'm thankful that people are still not falling dead

00:33:26.080 --> 00:33:29.500
as Ananias and Sapphira did over this situation.

00:33:30.399 --> 00:33:32.580
But can I tell you that our God is holy?

00:33:33.539 --> 00:33:34.619
Our God is holy.

00:33:36.159 --> 00:33:39.119
Some of us today in 2025 could look at Acts chapter number

00:33:39.119 --> 00:33:41.959
five and we could say, what's the big deal?

00:33:43.879 --> 00:33:48.639
Because quite honestly, in our culture and in our society,

00:33:48.639 --> 00:33:51.940
and unfortunately it's crept into the church house as well,

00:33:51.940 --> 00:33:56.940
honesty is not that high of a character trait.

00:33:58.360 --> 00:34:02.459
Many people today expect that people are lying to them.

00:34:02.459 --> 00:34:05.519
They just accept it as part of life.

00:34:05.519 --> 00:34:07.679
You watch the news, you listen to politicians,

00:34:07.679 --> 00:34:09.860
you just know that they're lying to you.

00:34:09.860 --> 00:34:10.799
We just accept it.

00:34:12.039 --> 00:34:13.199
I think it was eight years ago,

00:34:13.199 --> 00:34:15.899
I read a poll during an election cycle

00:34:15.899 --> 00:34:17.679
that there were only 48% of the people

00:34:17.679 --> 00:34:19.440
that were polled in this particular poll

00:34:19.440 --> 00:34:22.880
that actually expected the candidates to tell the truth.

00:34:22.880 --> 00:34:24.880
That means 52% of them that were polled

00:34:24.880 --> 00:34:27.119
expected that they were being lied to

00:34:27.119 --> 00:34:29.000
and they were okay with it.

00:34:29.000 --> 00:34:29.839
It's bizarre.

00:34:30.799 --> 00:34:33.600
Our God's holy, how do we respond?

00:34:34.880 --> 00:34:39.880
See, Exodus 920 and Exodus 921

00:34:41.639 --> 00:34:45.160
described for us the response to something

00:34:45.160 --> 00:34:46.799
that was extremely clear

00:34:46.799 --> 00:34:49.279
that God communicated and revealed.

00:34:49.279 --> 00:34:52.119
Here's what I'm gonna do, here's when I'm gonna do it,

00:34:52.119 --> 00:34:53.479
here's what you need to do.

00:34:55.119 --> 00:34:56.679
And so how do we respond?

00:34:56.679 --> 00:35:01.679
We read of two very different responses

00:35:02.119 --> 00:35:04.639
in verse 20 and verse 21.

00:35:04.639 --> 00:35:05.479
What did he tell them?

00:35:05.479 --> 00:35:07.199
Do it now, right?

00:35:07.199 --> 00:35:08.760
Do not delay.

00:35:08.760 --> 00:35:10.880
When's the best time to respond to God

00:35:10.880 --> 00:35:12.399
when he's speaking to you?

00:35:12.399 --> 00:35:13.799
Now.

00:35:13.799 --> 00:35:14.639
No delay.

00:35:15.239 --> 00:35:17.199
I'll say yes, Lord, yes.

00:35:17.199 --> 00:35:18.559
I'm gonna do what you tell me to do,

00:35:18.559 --> 00:35:21.559
I'm gonna respond, I'm gonna be obedient.

00:35:21.559 --> 00:35:23.040
And so as we evaluate our lives

00:35:23.040 --> 00:35:26.519
and we consider every week that we have the opportunity

00:35:26.519 --> 00:35:29.399
to hear God's word taught and God's word preached

00:35:29.399 --> 00:35:31.880
and every day of our lives that we have the opportunity

00:35:31.880 --> 00:35:34.320
to open the Bible and we're expecting

00:35:34.320 --> 00:35:38.320
that God is gonna use his passage to speak to his people

00:35:38.320 --> 00:35:40.239
and he's going to use his word.

00:35:40.239 --> 00:35:42.959
The Holy Spirit of God uses the word of God

00:35:42.959 --> 00:35:47.479
in the hearts of his people and how do we respond to it?

00:35:48.799 --> 00:35:53.679
Are we doers of the word or do we just kinda like,

00:35:53.679 --> 00:35:54.679
yeah, that was good.

00:35:55.559 --> 00:35:57.040
Check the box.

00:35:57.040 --> 00:35:58.600
Read my Bible today.

00:35:58.600 --> 00:36:00.559
Heard the message this week.

00:36:00.559 --> 00:36:02.919
Yep, that was good for so-and-so, I'm glad they were there.

00:36:02.919 --> 00:36:04.160
Maybe I need to get a copy of that

00:36:04.160 --> 00:36:07.239
and send it to so-and-so because they really need that.

00:36:07.239 --> 00:36:10.839
And we miss the fact that it's me, it's me, it's me,

00:36:10.839 --> 00:36:15.839
oh Lord, that needs what God has given to us.

00:36:16.440 --> 00:36:18.119
How do we respond?

00:36:18.119 --> 00:36:23.119
Our response to God is so vital, so very important

00:36:24.559 --> 00:36:27.880
and it must be that we respond in obedience

00:36:27.880 --> 00:36:30.679
as doers of the word and not hearers only.

00:36:30.679 --> 00:36:31.519
Let's pray.

00:36:31.519 --> 00:36:34.040
Father, we love you tonight.

00:36:34.040 --> 00:36:35.839
We thank you for loving us.

00:36:36.760 --> 00:36:39.119
We thank you for the truth of your word.

00:36:39.119 --> 00:36:42.440
As we look at this Old Testament account

00:36:42.440 --> 00:36:46.679
that illustrates so beautifully for us human nature

00:36:49.839 --> 00:36:51.239
throughout human history,

00:36:52.359 --> 00:36:56.359
that even here today, July of 2025,

00:36:59.559 --> 00:37:04.279
that we as your people who would readily admit

00:37:04.279 --> 00:37:05.679
that we expect to hear from you

00:37:05.679 --> 00:37:07.320
when we enter into a church service,

00:37:07.320 --> 00:37:09.600
when we open your word to read it personally,

00:37:11.079 --> 00:37:14.239
don't always respond as we ought.

00:37:16.559 --> 00:37:18.799
We do not always find ourselves in the category

00:37:18.799 --> 00:37:22.559
of those mentioned in verse 20 of our text.

00:37:23.679 --> 00:37:27.720
Sometimes, unfortunately, we're like those in verse 21,

00:37:29.519 --> 00:37:31.919
justifying our disobedience

00:37:31.919 --> 00:37:33.639
through whatever means it may be,

00:37:34.639 --> 00:37:36.559
not thinking that the consequences

00:37:36.559 --> 00:37:41.119
will actually come to realization.

00:37:42.320 --> 00:37:45.679
As we found in our text of scripture this evening,

00:37:45.679 --> 00:37:48.239
you do what you say you will do.

00:37:49.639 --> 00:37:51.320
God, I want personally,

00:37:51.320 --> 00:37:54.760
and I hope that those here tonight want personally

00:37:54.760 --> 00:37:57.000
your hand of blessing in our lives

00:37:58.320 --> 00:37:59.839
for our church corporately.

00:38:00.839 --> 00:38:04.479
And God, I pray that you'd help us to respond to you

00:38:04.479 --> 00:38:08.359
each time we enter into the church house

00:38:08.359 --> 00:38:11.639
and each time we enter into our personal devotion time

00:38:12.600 --> 00:38:15.399
that we'd respond in obedience,

00:38:15.399 --> 00:38:17.799
that we'd just determine to be doers of the word.

00:38:19.239 --> 00:38:20.239
Bless our time of prayer.

00:38:20.239 --> 00:38:22.359
We thank you for the privilege.

00:38:22.359 --> 00:38:25.320
It's in Christ's name we pray, amen.

00:38:25.320 --> 00:38:26.600
Let's look at the back of the prayer bulletin,

00:38:26.600 --> 00:38:28.559
if you would, and I bring it to you.

